{
  "local_port": 39440,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does an IFS officer get paid?",
  "response": "The salary of an Indian Foreign Service (IFS) officer is determined by the 7th Central Pay Commission and varies depending on their rank, experience, and allowances. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the approximate salary structure for an IFS officer:\n\n### **Basic Pay**\n1. **Junior Grade (Under Secretary / Third Secretary)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b956,100 per month (Level 10 of the Pay Matrix).\n2. **Senior Grade (Deputy Secretary / Second Secretary)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b967,700 per month (Level 11 of the Pay Matrix).\n3. **Junior Administrative Grade (Director / First Secretary)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b978,800 per month (Level 12 of the Pay Matrix).\n4. **Selection Grade (Counselor / Consul General)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b91,18,500 per month (Level 13 of the Pay Matrix).\n5. **Senior Administrative Grade (Joint Secretary / Ambassador)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b91,44,200 per month (Level 14 of the Pay Matrix).\n6. **Higher Administrative Grade (Additional Secretary / Ambassador)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b91,82,200 per month (Level 15 of the Pay Matrix).\n7. **Apex Scale (Secretary / Foreign Secretary)**:  \n   - Basic Pay: \u20b92,25,000 per month (Level 17 of the Pay Matrix).\n\n### **Allowances**\nIn addition to the basic pay, IFS officers receive various allowances, which significantly increase their take-home salary. These include:\n1. **Dearness Allowance (DA)**: Adjusted periodically based on inflation, currently around 31% of basic pay.\n2. **House Rent Allowance (HRA)**: Varies depending on the city of posting (e.g., 24% in metro cities, 16% in smaller cities).\n3. **Foreign Allowance**: Applicable for postings abroad, varies by country and is intended to cover living expenses.\n4. **Conveyance Allowance**: For transportation needs.\n5. **Medical Allowance**: For healthcare expenses.\n6. **Special Compensatory Allowance**: For hardship postings.\n7. **Other Perks**: Includes subsidized housing, official vehicles, and diplomatic privileges.\n\n### **Approximate Gross Salary**\nFor an entry-level IFS officer (Under Secretary / Third Secretary), the gross salary (including basic pay and allowances) is approximately **\u20b91,00,000 to \u20b91,30,000 per month**. For higher ranks, the gross salary can range from **\u20b92,00,000 to \u20b93,50,000 per month** or more, depending on the posting and rank.\n\n### **Foreign Postings**\nFor postings abroad, the salary increases significantly due to higher foreign allowances, which are based on the cost of living in the host country. In some cases, the total compensation can be much higher than domestic postings.\n\n### **Note**\nSalaries and allowances are subject to revisions by the government based on recommendations from the Pay Commission or other authorities.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for precise figures, it\u2019s advisable to consult the latest government notifications or official sources.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
